The paper discusses unsupervised pre-training of deep architectures for feature generation, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically falls under the sub-category of "Learning". The use of Stacked Denoising Autoencoders (SdA) and deep neural networks also suggests a focus on "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The application of these techniques to improve SVM classification accuracy suggests a focus on "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) and "Natural Language Processing" (cs.CL).
